Subject: [PATCH] tools/ps3load: use <stdbool.h>, not a false/true enum

GCC 15 (and C23 generally) promotes true and false to keywords, so
the old typedef enum { false, true } bool; now fails to compile.
Replace with <stdbool.h>; semantically identical and portable back
to C99.

diff --git a/tools/ps3load/source/main.c b/tools/ps3load/source/main.c
index 78e8539..deb22e0 100644
--- a/tools/ps3load/source/main.c
+++ b/tools/ps3load/source/main.c
@@ -65,7 +65,7 @@ typedef signed short s16;
 typedef signed int s32;
 typedef signed long long s64;
 
-typedef enum { false, true } bool;
+#include <stdbool.h>
 
 
 static const char *envvar = "PS3LOAD";
